For 'Failed to import Git' - Try downloading git , and adding git.exe to your Path
For 'Key Error' - Try setting tracking URI with registered scheme 'file' before run
mlflow.set_tracking_uri("file:/C:/Users/mlflow-masters/mlruns")

Windows support isn't great yet. The problem about the key error here is that your path, `C:\Users\\mlflow-master\mlruns`, starts with ´C:´ and MLFlow thinks that is the storing scheme. 
To fix that, prefacing the path with `file://` might work, but I'm not sure.
This PR adds support for windows paths: https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/pull/1171
